00:34:28,230 --> 00:34:31,190
Don't put it like that. It hurts me.

562
00:34:34,200 --> 00:34:35,690
What's this?

563
00:34:35,700 --> 00:34:37,490
What do you mean?

564
00:34:37,500 --> 00:34:40,350
You kept getting texts all night.

565
00:34:41,160 --> 00:34:43,450
Why did you read my texts?

566
00:34:43,460 --> 00:34:47,120
And why did you call me so many times?

567
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:48,540
I told you I was going out.

568
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:50,820
What do you do when you go out?

569
00:34:50,830 --> 00:34:54,620
Manger, you're sexy.
You're amazing.

570
00:34:55,250 --> 00:34:56,710
- You want to know?
- Yes.

571
00:34:56,730 --> 00:34:59,250
Why don't you show me?

572
00:34:59,250 --> 00:35:01,380
I will!

573
00:35:08,020 --> 00:35:11,090
- So?
- I can't believe this.

574
00:35:12,660 --> 00:35:15,450
Going through my phone is vile.

575
00:35:15,460 --> 00:35:17,550
Don't do it again.

576
00:35:17,560 --> 00:35:18,650
Vile?

577
00:35:18,660 --> 00:35:21,650
Yes. Have I ever done that?

578
00:35:21,660 --> 00:35:23,690
I don't have a mobile phone.

579
00:35:23,700 --> 00:35:26,320
Everyone has one but me!

580
00:35:26,330 --> 00:35:27,190
So?

581
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:29,990
Are you upset?

582
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:31,120
Uh, no.

583
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:35,850
Don't hang around with those women and spread gossip about people.

584
00:35:35,850 --> 00:35:38,380
They just gossip about the neighbors.

585
00:35:38,390 --> 00:35:40,480
Don't do it, okay?

586
00:35:40,500 --> 00:35:42,850
And stop watching so many dramas.

587
00:35:42,850 --> 00:35:44,190
Read newspapers.

588
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:46,550
Don't you even read books?

589
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:47,780
If I don't watch dramas,

590
00:35:47,790 --> 00:35:48,980
they won't let me hang out.

591
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:49,820
What?

592
00:35:49,830 --> 00:35:52,220
I don't have any friends now.

593
00:35:52,230 --> 00:35:54,390
They're the only ones who hang out with me.

594
00:35:55,230 --> 00:35:57,690
But you're not a woman!

595
00:35:57,700 --> 00:35:59,240
I'm half woman.

596
00:36:00,930 --> 00:36:01,840
Eat.

597
00:36:12,230 --> 00:36:13,150
Mom.

598
00:36:13,160 --> 00:36:14,190
Let's go.

599
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:15,690
No, I have to work.

600
00:36:15,700 --> 00:36:17,840
You're not working here. Come!

601
00:36:17,850 --> 00:36:20,710
Mom, don't do this.

602
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:22,510
Come!

603
00:36:23,250 --> 00:36:24,280
You.

604
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:26,110
Ouch.

605
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:27,380
This isn't going to work.

606
00:36:27,390 --> 00:36:29,420
This will! Enroll, now!

607
00:36:29,430 --> 00:36:31,610
We can't afford to pay college tuition!

608
00:36:31,620 --> 00:36:34,780
I'll find the money, no matter what,

609
00:36:34,790 --> 00:36:35,880
so take classes here.

610
00:36:35,890 --> 00:36:37,580
I got a full scholarship.

611
00:36:37,600 --> 00:36:40,280
You won't have to pay anything.

612
00:36:40,290 --> 00:36:42,110
Mom, I'm going to become a captain.

613
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:43,740
I don't want to become a judge.

614
00:36:43,750 --> 00:36:45,240
Don't you understand?

615
00:36:45,250 --> 00:36:46,320
Please let me do this.

616
00:36:46,330 --> 00:36:48,720
Don't you understand me?

617
00:36:48,730 --> 00:36:50,850
Can't you let me win this once?

618
00:36:50,850 --> 00:36:52,840
Please do this for me.

619
00:36:52,850 --> 00:36:57,240
You want me to live in that rat hole?

620
00:36:57,250 --> 00:36:59,240
If you become a judge, it'll go away.

621
00:36:59,250 --> 00:37:01,780
You can save everyone.

622
00:37:01,790 --> 00:37:02,920
Mom.

623
00:37:02,930 --> 00:37:04,990
Becoming a judge isn't winning the lottery.

624
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:07,620
Even if I become a judge, I won't be rich.

625
00:37:07,620 --> 00:37:10,210
Shut up! Come with me!

626
00:37:10,230 --> 00:37:11,750
Oh, my! Hey!

627
00:37:19,250 --> 00:37:21,690
Father,

628
00:37:21,700 --> 00:37:23,220
I'm sorry

629
00:37:23,230 --> 00:37:24,950
I didn't tell you before.

630
00:37:24,960 --> 00:37:27,350
You know why your mom's acting like that.

631
00:37:28,350 --> 00:37:29,880
I do.

632
00:37:31,020 --> 00:37:34,420
If I knew this would happen,

633
00:37:34,430 --> 00:37:36,880
I would've done what she wanted,

634
00:37:36,890 --> 00:37:40,690
no matter what my dream was.

635
00:37:40,700 --> 00:37:43,690
But I decided before all this.

636
00:37:44,330 --> 00:37:46,220
What do you want to do?

637
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:49,610
I don't know.

638
00:37:50,730 --> 00:37:54,490
I want to become a captain,

639
00:37:54,500 --> 00:37:58,750
but with mom acting like that,

640
00:37:58,750 --> 00:38:04,710
I'm thinking maybe I should go back to studying.

641
00:38:06,020 --> 00:38:10,050
Father, what should I do?

642
00:38:10,060 --> 00:38:12,120
Life is long.

643
00:38:12,120 --> 00:38:13,580
Look further down the line.

644
00:38:13,600 --> 00:38:19,820
Choose the path you won't regret after 10 or 20 years.

645
00:38:20,750 --> 00:38:25,840
I don't care what choices you make.

646
00:38:25,850 --> 00:38:32,820
You can follow your dream or you can become a judge.

647
00:38:33,620 --> 00:38:35,840
Make a list

648
00:38:35,850 --> 00:38:38,420
of the pros and cons for taking one path

649
00:38:38,430 --> 00:38:41,320
and taking the other path.

650
00:38:41,330 --> 00:38:44,920
Then you'll get the answer.

651
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:50,340
Only you can make this decision.

652
00:38:50,350 --> 00:38:51,880
It's your life.

653
00:39:05,790 --> 00:39:07,340
[Family Registration]

654
00:39:13,750 --> 00:39:15,050
Hello.

655
00:39:15,060 --> 00:39:16,490
Have a seat over there.

656
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:17,750
We want two soft tofu stews.

657
00:39:17,750 --> 00:39:18,820
Okay.

658
00:39:18,830 --> 00:39:20,510
- Two soft tofu stews.
- Okay.

659
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:21,840
- Make them extra good.
- Okay.

660
00:39:25,700 --> 00:39:27,740
[Minjung]

661
00:39:33,390 --> 00:39:34,240
Hello?

662
00:39:34,250 --> 00:39:35,690
It's me.

663
00:39:35,700 --> 00:39:37,320
Where are you?

664
00:39:37,330 --> 00:39:40,650
The court sent documents.
We should meet.

665
00:39:40,660 --> 00:39:42,690
Come get the soft tofu.

666
00:39:43,890 --> 00:39:46,380
What are you doing?
You're working!

667
00:39:46,390 --> 00:39:47,690
You can take care of it.

668
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:03,990
[Seoul Family Court]

669
00:40:08,890 --> 00:40:11,010
Here are my divorce papers.

670
00:40:11,020 --> 00:40:11,920
Okay.

671
00:40:34,350 --> 00:40:36,580
Did you process the document I gave you?

672
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:37,490
No, not yet.

673
00:40:37,500 --> 00:40:39,650
When's the deadline?

674
00:40:39,660 --> 00:40:41,010
It's today.

675
00:40:42,430 --> 00:40:45,380
If it's not processed today, it'll be nullified.

676
00:40:45,390 --> 00:40:46,510
You won't be divorced.

677
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:01,220
No, mom.

678
00:41:01,230 --> 00:41:04,390
But I can see Subak doing it.

679
00:41:04,390 --> 00:41:06,540
Subak did what?

680
00:41:06,560 --> 00:41:09,090
Minjung is really acting really suspiciously.

681
00:41:09,790 --> 00:41:12,050
Why would he get a divorce?

682
00:41:12,060 --> 00:41:13,990
Why don't you find out who she is?

683
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:16,990
Why do you want to know? It's over.

684
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:20,390
If Minjung has a woman, they can't divorce.

685
00:41:20,390 --> 00:41:23,880
It's not like Subak is innocent.

686
00:41:23,890 --> 00:41:24,980
What do you mean?

687
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:27,550
She made a mistake before getting married.

688
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:29,620
You can't call that a mistake!

689
00:41:29,620 --> 00:41:33,980
It wasn't like she was engaged to him before she moved in with him.

690
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:36,950
She just did, without thinking about it,

691
00:41:36,960 --> 00:41:39,290
or even finishing college.

692
00:41:39,290 --> 00:41:41,190
What she did was terrible.

693
00:41:41,200 --> 00:41:43,740
Minjung married her because he didn't know.

694
00:41:43,750 --> 00:41:46,610
He wouldn't have, if he knew.
Nobody would.

695
00:41:46,620 --> 00:41:49,940
If Sedal did that, I couldn't forgive him.

696
00:41:59,230 --> 00:42:00,320
Please process this.

697
00:42:00,330 --> 00:42:01,490
Okay.

698
00:42:09,560 --> 00:42:12,510
Your divorce paper has been processed.

699
00:42:12,520 --> 00:42:14,780
So I'm divorced now?

700
00:42:14,790 --> 00:42:15,840
Yes.

701
00:42:15,850 --> 00:42:19,420
You almost didn't make it.

702
00:42:19,430 --> 00:42:22,240
I can't say this was right or wrong, though.

703
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:30,990
Minjung.

704
00:42:37,750 --> 00:42:39,840
Congratulate me.

705
00:42:40,500 --> 00:42:42,750
I'm finally divorced.

706
00:42:44,100 --> 00:42:45,780
You submitted the documents?

707
00:42:45,790 --> 00:42:47,090
Yes.

708
00:42:47,100 --> 00:42:49,090
It was really simple.

709
00:42:49,100 --> 00:42:51,190
Making up my mind was hard,

710
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:54,720
but all it took was submitting the paper.

711
00:42:54,730 --> 00:42:56,590
How do you feel?

712
00:42:56,600 --> 00:42:58,190
Weird?

713
00:42:58,200 --> 00:43:00,420
Sort of.

714
00:43:02,290 --> 00:43:05,650
I'm relieved.

715
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:09,650
And also excited.

716
00:43:09,660 --> 00:43:12,550
I can really date you now.

717
00:43:13,250 --> 00:43:16,150
- I'm not falling for that.
- I'm serious.

718
00:43:16,160 --> 00:43:18,720
You and I have nothing to hold us back.

719
00:43:18,730 --> 00:43:21,750
You are a bad guy.

720
00:43:21,750 --> 00:43:24,380
You know how sad you made me?

721
00:43:24,390 --> 00:43:26,510
- How?
- You told me to go.

722
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:28,710
And you kept breaking up with me.

723
00:43:28,730 --> 00:43:30,250
I did?

724
00:43:30,250 --> 00:43:31,820
See?

725
00:43:31,830 --> 00:43:35,950
Classic. You forgot everything you did.

726
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:39,450
You turned to me when your father was sick,

727
00:43:39,460 --> 00:43:42,290
saying, "Sunjeong, stay with me."

728
00:43:42,290 --> 00:43:45,280
But when your father got better,

729
00:43:45,290 --> 00:43:48,280
you tossed me a hair pin and told me you couldn't see me.

730
00:43:48,290 --> 00:43:51,990
I must be mad to come and go as you say.

731
00:43:56,290 --> 00:43:59,440
I really am a mean bastard.

732
00:43:59,460 --> 00:44:01,490
Why do you keep following me around?

733
00:44:01,500 --> 00:44:03,020
I didn't follow you around.

734
00:44:03,020 --> 00:44:05,280
You just appeared.

735
00:44:07,000 --> 00:44:10,020
That's how you are.

736
00:44:10,020 --> 00:44:12,380
And I like you that way.

737
00:44:12,390 --> 00:44:14,650
You only look at one direction.

738
00:44:14,660 --> 00:44:17,590
You never failed your family.

739
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:21,740
You made me cry but that's who you are.

740
00:44:21,750 --> 00:44:23,820
When we dated, the whole 7 years,

741
00:44:23,830 --> 00:44:26,120
you never looked at another woman.

742
00:44:26,120 --> 00:44:28,940
You always remained faithful.

743
00:44:29,700 --> 00:44:32,450
And I really loved you for that.

744
00:44:32,460 --> 00:44:34,050
For being so consistent.

745
00:44:37,500 --> 00:44:39,520
Congratulations, anyway.

746
00:44:40,390 --> 00:44:42,240
Thanks.

747
00:44:42,250 --> 00:44:46,240
I would've had soju alone at home.

748
00:44:46,250 --> 00:44:48,740
But I'm happy to see you.

749
00:44:48,750 --> 00:44:50,740
Maybe we should have a party.

750
00:44:50,750 --> 00:44:52,420
We're both divorced.

751
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:55,690
Be honest with me.

752
00:44:55,700 --> 00:44:58,920
You were waiting for this to happen, right?

753
00:44:58,930 --> 00:45:00,510
How can you say that?

754
00:45:01,460 --> 00:45:02,690
How did you know?

755
00:45:02,700 --> 00:45:04,720
I held my breath until my neck turned stiff.

756
00:45:05,390 --> 00:45:06,340
Look.

757
00:45:19,790 --> 00:45:21,440
[Provisional Attachment Notice]

758
00:45:44,620 --> 00:45:46,080
[Seoul Family Court]

759
00:45:58,000 --> 00:45:59,950
[Form: Divorce by Consent]

760
00:46:20,960 --> 00:46:22,350
I did that?

761
00:46:22,350 --> 00:46:24,690
You did. I'll be right back.

762
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:34,890
Hello, mother.

763
00:46:34,890 --> 00:46:37,110
Minjung, what are you doing?

764
00:46:37,830 --> 00:46:39,780
I had plans, so I'm out.

765
00:46:39,790 --> 00:46:41,440
Did you have dinner?

766
00:46:42,350 --> 00:46:44,150
Yes.

767
00:46:44,160 --> 00:46:46,840
Have you been busy?
You haven't visited.

768
00:46:46,850 --> 00:46:49,610
Aeji and Jungji want their dad.

769
00:46:49,620 --> 00:46:50,740
Minjung.

770
00:46:56,060 --> 00:46:58,620
I'll drop by tomorrow.

771
00:46:59,890 --> 00:47:01,420
Okay.

772
00:47:01,430 --> 00:47:03,720
Minjung, please come tomorrow.

773
00:47:03,730 --> 00:47:06,090
Don't you feel bad for your kids?

774
00:47:06,100 --> 00:47:10,240
Their mom is gone, so you should visit.

775
00:47:11,020 --> 00:47:12,550
Goodbye, then.

776
00:47:18,390 --> 00:47:22,440
Don't call Minjung so often.

777
00:47:22,460 --> 00:47:26,220
I call him because of the kids.

778
00:47:26,230 --> 00:47:28,150
Don't use the kids as an excuse.

779
00:47:28,160 --> 00:47:29,380
It'll make him uncomfortable.

780
00:47:29,390 --> 00:47:31,040
Why would it?

781
00:47:31,060 --> 00:47:35,150
He hasn't come so I just got curious.

782
00:47:35,160 --> 00:47:38,240
He's all alone so I'm worried.

783
00:47:38,250 --> 00:47:40,210
He can take care of himself.

784
00:47:40,230 --> 00:47:43,290
I know why you're doing it but stop.

785
00:47:43,290 --> 00:47:45,510
Their divorce has been finalized.

786
00:47:45,520 --> 00:47:47,880
It hasn't yet.

787
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:54,620
What's this?

788
00:47:54,620 --> 00:47:57,110
Divorce confirmation.

789
00:47:57,120 --> 00:47:59,310
This was in the mail.

790
00:47:59,330 --> 00:48:02,280
Minjung must have gotten it already.

791
00:48:02,290 --> 00:48:04,880
If he submitted it, they'd be divorced.

792
00:48:04,890 --> 00:48:08,190
So stop calling him so often.

793
00:48:08,200 --> 00:48:11,050
And the kids are our grandchildren.

794
00:48:22,160 --> 00:48:24,190
[Mom]

795
00:48:30,560 --> 00:48:31,650
Let's go.

796
00:48:32,200 --> 00:48:34,220
Where should we go?

797
00:48:34,230 --> 00:48:35,920
Let me think.

798
00:48:35,930 --> 00:48:37,950
We should walk a little.

799
00:48:37,960 --> 00:48:41,740
I came right away because you said you were having a bad day.

800
00:48:41,750 --> 00:48:44,420
It's not just tonight.

801
00:48:44,430 --> 00:48:48,010
Kids are useless. All of them.

802
00:48:48,020 --> 00:48:50,050
It's cold.

803
00:48:52,000 --> 00:48:53,790
Where do you want to go?

804
00:48:53,790 --> 00:48:55,880
Somewhere crowded. Somewhere tight.

805
00:48:55,890 --> 00:48:57,440
What?

806
00:48:57,460 --> 00:49:00,890
It's cold, so let's go somewhere really crowded.

807
00:49:00,890 --> 00:49:04,210
I want to go where there is no one around.

808
00:49:04,230 --> 00:49:06,350
But that's boring.

809
00:49:22,100 --> 00:49:23,450
How do you feel?
Warm, right?

810
00:49:23,460 --> 00:49:24,390
Yes.

811
00:49:24,390 --> 00:49:26,840
I love it when someone holds me.

812
00:49:26,850 --> 00:49:29,150
Be them my hands or my shoulders.

813
00:49:29,160 --> 00:49:32,050
It's pretty interesting here.

814
00:49:32,060 --> 00:49:33,550
Isn't it?

815
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:36,010
I'm not unhappy anymore.

816
00:49:36,020 --> 00:49:37,550
Tell me if you get hungry.

817
00:49:37,560 --> 00:49:40,650
I'm not hungry. Let's walk some more.

818
00:49:52,200 --> 00:49:54,420
I feel so relieved now.

819
00:50:05,290 --> 00:50:07,320
The divorce paper arrived.

820
00:50:07,330 --> 00:50:11,620
See Minjung and beg him to forgive you.

821
00:50:11,620 --> 00:50:14,150
You have to think about the kids.

822
00:50:33,620 --> 00:50:35,210
Sunjeong, we're leaving.

823
00:50:35,230 --> 00:50:36,620
Have a nice day, Daese.

824
00:50:36,620 --> 00:50:38,380
Have a good day, father.

825
00:50:38,390 --> 00:50:39,840
Aunt, I'll see you later.

826
00:50:47,930 --> 00:50:50,780
I think I'll have to go to China soon.

827
00:50:50,790 --> 00:50:51,780
Okay.

828
00:50:51,790 --> 00:50:54,820
Sign the contract while you're there.

829
00:50:54,830 --> 00:50:55,850
I should.

830
00:50:59,890 --> 00:51:00,740
Aunt?

831
00:51:01,790 --> 00:51:03,740
Now?

832
00:51:03,750 --> 00:51:04,920
Okay.

833
00:51:08,020 --> 00:51:09,280
Is that true?

834
00:51:09,290 --> 00:51:10,880
Yes.

835
00:51:10,890 --> 00:51:13,310
Gwangbak told me to keep it a secret,

836
00:51:13,330 --> 00:51:15,150
but I can't do it.

837
00:51:16,660 --> 00:51:18,690
How could that happen?

838
00:51:19,790 --> 00:51:21,340
They had to move?

839
00:51:21,350 --> 00:51:22,810
Yes.

840
00:51:22,830 --> 00:51:25,120
They moved to a tiny two room house.

841
00:51:25,120 --> 00:51:27,880
